After all,

273
00:18:24,620 --> 00:18:28,160
we were nothing but just a fake couple.

274
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:32,580
Keeping the baby

275
00:18:32,580 --> 00:18:35,640
isn't a light decision to make, you know.

276
00:18:51,780 --> 00:18:52,420
Here.

277
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:56,500
You've done well.

278
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:58,820
I'm impressed.

279
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:15,560
Thank you.

280
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:23,520
It's complicated, those two.

281
00:19:26,380 --> 00:19:27,260
Yes.

282
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:36,040
The landlady.

283
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:38,380
Can I have a word with you?

284
00:19:38,380 --> 00:19:42,340
Oh, Shiori-san, perfect timing.

285
00:19:42,580 --> 00:19:46,960
I ordered your wedding kimono
from Shirafuji-ya.

286
00:19:47,140 --> 00:19:50,800
Let's have the ceremony as soon as possible.

287
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,540
About that...

288
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,100
I...

289
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,400
I still can't marry Tsubaki-san.

290
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:04,080
The truth is...

291
00:20:04,980 --> 00:20:08,040
Because you're not pregnant?

292
00:20:09,740 --> 00:20:12,100
Did you know that? Sorry!

293
00:20:12,100 --> 00:20:14,640
I will talk to my father about this.

294
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:18,140
Shiori-san. It's okay. It's not like that.

295
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:20,880
You can always do something about it later.

296
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:25,460
If not Tsubaki, then someone else.

297
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:28,220
It doesn't matter who you're with,

298
00:20:28,220 --> 00:20:30,220
Just get pregnant.

299
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:32,260
I told you.

300
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:35,980
Things change when you have children.

301
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:38,720
You can be happy!

302
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,460
I don't want to!

303
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:42,460
Why not?

304
00:20:42,820 --> 00:20:46,540
Please, Shiori-san! Neh, please...

305
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:51,860
Shiori-san, clean up the shop, please.

306
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:53,360
Wait...

307
00:20:53,360 --> 00:20:54,680
Would you stop

308
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:56,160
dragging others into this?

309
00:20:57,660 --> 00:20:59,440
Can you make it?

310
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:02,960
Sweets to impress your grandfather.

311
00:21:03,460 --> 00:21:06,600
What if he chooses that little girl's sweets?

312
00:21:06,860 --> 00:21:08,680
I refuse to accept it.

313
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:12,420
That woman took Itsuki-san away from me.

314
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:15,060
Now she's taken Kougetsuan away too.

315
00:21:15,060 --> 00:21:16,520
Nao doesn't think her mom did it.

316
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:18,520
It was the woman who killed her.

317
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:22,100
The police said
there were fingerprints on the knife.

318
00:21:24,780 --> 00:21:26,740
I won't give it.

319
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:32,180
Not to that girl!

320
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:36,200
Let's go cancel this competition.

321
00:21:36,260 --> 00:21:37,400
No...

322
00:21:40,660 --> 00:21:41,680
Tsubaki?

323
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:44,640
Don't do anything.

324
00:21:45,220 --> 00:21:46,620
Not to Shiori-san and not to Nao-san.

325
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:51,080
If you do anything in the slightest,
I'm out of this game.

326
00:21:54,660 --> 00:21:57,360
I'm going to win this game.

327
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:06,440
(December 29th)

328
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:08,140
(December 29th)
It's the 29th already.

329
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,240
New Year's Eve is in 2 days.

330
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:11,280
Yes.

331
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:16,360
Now that you know you misunderstood Tsubaki-kun,

332
00:22:17,660 --> 00:22:20,160
are you having second thoughts?

333
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,820
Of course not.

334
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:28,240
You're still a terrible liar, Nao-chan.

335
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:32,220
The day after tomorrow's game
will decide who will take over Kougetsuan.

336
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:35,760
But is that really how it ends?

337
00:22:36,140 --> 00:22:38,180
Between Nao-chan and Tsubaki-kun.

338
00:22:38,860 --> 00:22:43,180
Once the successor is chosen,

339
00:22:43,580 --> 00:22:46,180
You may never see him again, you know?

340
00:22:57,060 --> 00:22:58,500
I thought

341
00:22:59,160 --> 00:23:01,740
After Nao-san left Kogetsuan.

342
00:23:01,980 --> 00:23:04,940
you will start to enjoy making sweets.

343
00:23:05,780 --> 00:23:07,100
What are you talking about?

344
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,140
How long do you think you can keep up the pretence?

345
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:11,900
This last three years.

346
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:15,020
you've never once stopped loving her!

347
00:23:17,360 --> 00:23:19,920
Is this what you really want?

348
00:23:31,740 --> 00:23:34,920
Maybe I'm attracted to you.

349
00:23:36,960 --> 00:23:37,660
Nao.

350
00:23:39,770 --> 00:23:41,300
I like you.

351
00:23:47,980 --> 00:23:50,460
I just wanted to see Tsubaki.

352
00:23:53,510 --> 00:23:54,480
Thank you.

353
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:56,940
I'll wait for you.

354
00:23:57,040 --> 00:24:00,940
I'll wait you here, Tsubaki!

355
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:10,580
I'm coming back... to Nao's place.

356
00:24:49,060 --> 00:24:50,900
It look like it's going to snow.

357
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:52,880
Uhm.

358
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:07,860
When I was little,

359
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:11,960
I was weak and withdrawn.

360
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:15,200
Tsubaki was so cheerful.

361
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:19,800
When we're together, it's warm and dreamy...

362
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:21,280
Those days,

363
00:25:22,180 --> 00:25:25,940
I really liked Tsubaki.

364
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:28,660
But at the same time,

365
00:25:29,540 --> 00:25:31,780
there's a scene that always comes to mind.

366
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:36,180
That was Sakura's mom.

367
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:38,580
That scene

368
00:25:38,820 --> 00:25:42,040
makes me so inexplicably angry.

369
00:25:43,260 --> 00:25:47,560
I love you... but I can't forgive you.

370
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:58,640
Win or lose...

371
00:26:00,660 --> 00:26:03,480
The day after tomorrow will be our last.

372
00:26:06,040 --> 00:26:08,100
Make it last.

373
00:26:09,540 --> 00:26:11,720
I'll never see Tsubaki again.

374
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:30,120
I understand.

375
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:57,820
Don't cry.

376
00:26:58,050 --> 00:27:00,520
Or I won't be able to leave.

377
00:27:21,740 --> 00:27:23,080
Only at the end...

378
00:27:24,100 --> 00:27:28,380
Just for now, I want to be with Tsubaki.

379
00:27:59,020 --> 00:28:00,620
Tomorrow we'll celebrate the event.

380
00:28:01,080 --> 00:28:02,900
It'll be the day

381
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:05,620
our fate is decided.

382
00:28:11,620 --> 00:28:13,620
(December 31st)

383
00:28:15,980 --> 00:28:18,600
Okay, that's all.

384
00:28:18,780 --> 00:28:21,960
It's always nerve-wracking to put up the lanterns.

385
00:28:22,580 --> 00:28:25,200
It's God's pathway.

386
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:30,380
Who will Tsubaki-san and Nao-san smile at?

387
00:28:32,140 --> 00:28:33,800
If Tsubaki-san loses,

388
00:28:34,220 --> 00:28:36,800
will he leave this place?

389
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:40,760
He won't lose.

390
00:28:41,620 --> 00:28:44,380
Tsubaki-san knows everything about this shop.

391
00:28:45,140 --> 00:28:47,160
Nao-san can't beat that.

392
00:28:48,860 --> 00:28:51,160
Come on, let's go.

393
00:28:54,700 --> 00:28:56,180
Surprising.

394
00:28:56,860 --> 00:28:59,680
I can't believe you made it to today
without any interference.

395
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:05,180
I'm gonna win this fight.

396
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:09,480
Because I believe that my son will win.

397
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:27,120
Yes, please.

398
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:29,480
Yes, I'm prepared.

399
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:32,940
Please proceed as soon as possible.

400
00:29:48,300 --> 00:29:51,080
Excuse me.

401
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:06,840
Let's see what you two have brought.

402
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:08,000
Yes.

403
00:30:08,260 --> 00:30:09,360
Yes.

404
00:30:09,780 --> 00:30:12,360
First one is Sakura.

405
00:30:14,180 --> 00:30:17,480
Let's start with your sweets.

406
00:30:20,280 --> 00:30:22,220
Here you are.

407
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:34,260
"Yuzu sweets"

408
00:30:39,040 --> 00:30:40,280
This is....

409
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:44,980
Did you put the whole peel of the yuzu in?

410
00:30:47,180 --> 00:30:49,120
I used Hime Yuzu.

411
00:30:50,540 --> 00:30:52,180
I Hollowed out the inside.

412
00:30:52,260 --> 00:30:54,680
Extremely thin skin.

413
00:30:54,800 --> 00:30:58,120
Soaked in honey, filled with red bean paste.

414
00:30:58,260 --> 00:30:59,980
Incrusting it.

415
00:30:59,980 --> 00:31:01,460
(Winter Warm)

416
00:31:01,460 --> 00:31:04,340
The result is a beautiful looking kneaded cut.

417
00:31:10,540 --> 00:31:11,420
Hmmm!

418
00:31:15,140 --> 00:31:18,680
The texture of the crust melts in your mouth.

419
00:31:19,140 --> 00:31:24,100
A pleasant fragrance that lasts forever.

420
00:31:24,540 --> 00:31:28,560
Does the confinement of
the bowl leave a lingering aroma?

421
00:31:29,420 --> 00:31:31,700
A warm sweet.

422
00:31:32,780 --> 00:31:36,240
Like you want to be wrapped up forever.

423
00:31:37,780 --> 00:31:40,340
Warm sweets.

424
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:43,080
Mom,

425
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:47,600
why does the smell of the sweet disappear so fast?

426
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:51,720
Because it's inside your stomach.

427
00:31:54,420 --> 00:31:56,580
Let's make it one day.

428
00:31:56,840 --> 00:31:59,200
Sweets that don't make you feel lonely like that,

429
00:31:59,740 --> 00:32:01,480
with Mom.

430
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:04,820
Yes, promise!

431
00:32:09,220 --> 00:32:11,680
I was able to make it properly.

432
00:32:11,960 --> 00:32:14,840
Sweets that I think I like.

433
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:20,420
Next, let's have yours.

434
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:22,420
Yes.

435
00:32:31,080 --> 00:32:32,660
It's "Tsubaki Mochi".

436
00:32:34,740 --> 00:32:36,600
(Tsubaki Mochi)

437
00:32:37,020 --> 00:32:39,260
It appears in The Tale of Genji.

438
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:42,680
It's said to be the origin of Japanese sweets.

439
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:46,660
A simple camellia leaf sandwiching Domyoji.

440
00:32:48,140 --> 00:32:52,080
To think that Tsubaki would come
and make such a simple pastry.

441
00:33:00,840 --> 00:33:02,720
This taste...

442
00:33:03,700 --> 00:33:06,840
How do you know what this tastes like?

443
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:10,340
The taste I taught Itsuki.

444
00:33:11,820 --> 00:33:17,040
It was the first sweet I learnt from my father.

445
00:33:20,120 --> 00:33:21,620
Listen, Tsubaki?

446
00:33:22,220 --> 00:33:25,800
Our Domyoji is steamed with
a little bit of the heart left on.

447
00:33:25,960 --> 00:33:28,520
Your body will know
what it feels like to be steamed.

448
00:33:28,700 --> 00:33:29,340
Yes.

449
00:33:30,660 --> 00:33:34,140
You must have been taught
when you were really young.

450
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:36,500
How did you manage to recreate it exactly.

451
00:33:36,500 --> 00:33:41,620
I will never forget.
The taste means a lot to me.

452
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:51,840
Japanese sweets tell the story...

453
00:33:53,740 --> 00:33:55,520
It's not just about taste.

454
00:33:57,780 --> 00:34:00,180
The scene when it is in your mouth.

455
00:34:01,260 --> 00:34:03,040
A feeling.

456
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:09,420
A tender memory that was certainly there.

457
00:34:11,540 --> 00:34:15,980
I'm sure it's the same with you, Grandfather.

458
00:34:21,580 --> 00:34:23,620
Tsubaki, come here.

459
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:24,980
Yes!

460
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:29,300
That's it.

461
00:34:30,940 --> 00:34:33,120
It's been handed down from
generation to generation.

462
00:34:54,240 --> 00:34:59,180
They were both fantastic sweets.

463
00:35:01,240 --> 00:35:03,520
One more for me.

464
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:07,220
Let me think it over again.

465
00:35:08,540 --> 00:35:12,400
Tsubaki, you stay in the left room.

466
00:35:13,500 --> 00:35:16,180
Sakura, you stay in the right room.

467
00:35:17,060 --> 00:35:20,940
I will open the door belonging to my final choice.

468
00:35:47,660 --> 00:35:50,480
You can't just sit there and listen to them.

469
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:52,300
You won't hear a thing.

470
00:35:58,360 --> 00:36:01,140
I'll give you a chance.

471
00:36:03,420 --> 00:36:07,980
Choose the sweet which you think is
the most suitable for successor.

472
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:10,680
What?

473
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:14,540
I'm respecting your position as a landlady.

474
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:18,180
It's easy.

475
00:36:50,340 --> 00:36:52,100
I choose this one.

476
00:37:02,540 --> 00:37:06,280
If I win, my future is ahead of me.

477
00:37:09,580 --> 00:37:13,260
If I lose, I will have to give up

478
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:18,540
the important things I've believed in until now.

479
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:26,820
I'll leave Kougetsuan to you.

480
00:37:40,780 --> 00:37:44,320
I give it to you.

481
00:38:01,940 --> 00:38:05,740
Me? I will take over Kougetsuan...

482
00:38:06,100 --> 00:38:07,020
Why?

483
00:38:07,240 --> 00:38:10,000
I chose the yuzu confectionery.

484
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:12,680
Beautiful and elaborate looking pastries.

485
00:38:12,680 --> 00:38:15,680
Exactly what the Tsubaki made!

486
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:19,260
Tsubaki made "Tsubaki Mochi".

487
00:38:20,260 --> 00:38:23,540
The first sweet Itsuki taught him to make.

488
00:38:38,600 --> 00:38:39,660
Tsubaki.

489
00:38:43,420 --> 00:38:44,740
Tsubaki.

490
00:38:45,180 --> 00:38:49,140
You promised me, didn't you?
You said you'll win.

491
00:38:49,140 --> 00:38:51,080
Ne, Tsubaki!

492
00:38:51,800 --> 00:38:55,700
What do you think I gave birth to you for?

493
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:56,740
Stop it!

494
00:38:56,740 --> 00:38:58,680
I shouldn't have believed it!

495
00:38:58,680 --> 00:39:01,080
There were so many ways to do it!

496
00:39:01,080 --> 00:39:02,060
I won't stop...

497
00:39:05,020 --> 00:39:06,020
Grand Master!

498
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:07,880
Call an ambulance...

499
00:39:07,980 --> 00:39:09,140
Don't call.

500
00:39:11,480 --> 00:39:14,560
No more... hospitals.

501
00:39:18,080 --> 00:39:19,000
Grandfather.

502
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:28,520
You must have been pushing yourself very hard.

503
00:39:35,060 --> 00:39:37,420
Sensei, is he...?

504
00:39:37,940 --> 00:39:41,240
He wants to talk to you.

505
00:39:41,800 --> 00:39:43,240
Tsubaki-san, alone.

506
00:39:53,370 --> 00:39:54,400
Tsubaki...

507
00:39:57,770 --> 00:40:01,170
Your "Tsubaki mochi",

508
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:05,340
it was really good.

509
00:40:07,340 --> 00:40:08,680
But...

510
00:40:10,050 --> 00:40:14,080
I couldn't pick yours.

511
00:40:16,820 --> 00:40:17,910
Because...

512
00:40:20,340 --> 00:40:24,220
That was a sweet made only for me.

513
00:40:29,050 --> 00:40:32,520
I've been always...

514
00:40:38,310 --> 00:40:40,910
wanted you to accept me.

515
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:48,340
I'm sorry... really.

516
00:40:51,370 --> 00:40:55,710
Neither I or Itsuki had the choice,

517
00:40:57,310 --> 00:41:03,880
but from now, you have all the freedom
to make any sweets you want.

518
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:08,200
You should

519
00:41:09,770 --> 00:41:13,420
Make sweets that are unique to you.

520
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:18,200
Without any restraints.

521
00:41:21,450 --> 00:41:23,420
As you think...

522
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:33,710
Grandfather.

523
00:41:34,540 --> 00:41:37,340
Grandfather... Grandfather!

524
00:41:37,820 --> 00:41:39,600
Please step back.

525
00:41:43,820 --> 00:41:45,370
Two times...

526
00:41:47,620 --> 00:41:49,570
You've only eaten two of my sweets.

527
00:41:50,420 --> 00:41:52,450
I'm going to make more for you.

528
00:41:52,910 --> 00:41:55,000
To make up for all the time we lost.

529
00:41:59,220 --> 00:42:00,880
I'm sorry.

530
00:42:15,340 --> 00:42:17,450
Grandfather...

531
00:42:38,370 --> 00:42:40,370
(Dear valued customer,
we are close for 5 days - Manager)

532
00:42:42,370 --> 00:42:45,970
It's finally time for
a new generation at Kougetsuan.

533
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:48,940
Tsubaki-san will take over, won't he?

534
00:42:49,340 --> 00:42:51,650
I heard that's not true.

535
00:42:51,880 --> 00:42:56,450
He said he couldn't take over Kougetsuan
because he wasn't his own grandson.

536
00:42:57,220 --> 00:42:59,340
Then why don't you come back to my house too?

537
00:42:59,740 --> 00:43:00,910
That's right,

538
00:43:01,110 --> 00:43:02,340
Father.

539
00:43:03,420 --> 00:43:04,370
Do what you want.

540
00:43:05,820 --> 00:43:06,880
Father...

541
00:43:15,680 --> 00:43:17,650
Now my family is...

542
00:43:17,970 --> 00:43:20,400
Really, there's no one left.

543
00:43:23,910 --> 00:43:24,880
Tsubaki-san...

544
00:43:35,710 --> 00:43:37,440
What are you wearing?

545
00:43:37,770 --> 00:43:39,510
What happened to your kimono?

546
00:43:42,400 --> 00:43:43,940
Thank you very much for your help.

547
00:43:45,450 --> 00:43:46,820
What?

548
00:44:05,340 --> 00:44:07,510
