Don't make a big deal out of it...
for the good of the shop...

867
01:09:21,910 --> 01:09:23,080
Itsuki-san.

868
01:09:24,510 --> 01:09:25,850
Kyoko.

869
01:09:28,620 --> 01:09:32,080
I'm really sorry about all this.

870
01:09:33,650 --> 01:09:37,800
I hurt you, I made you suffer.

871
01:09:38,820 --> 01:09:40,000
Itsuki-san.

872
01:09:41,480 --> 01:09:45,570
Please take care of Tsubaki... and this shop.

873
01:09:46,570 --> 01:09:50,140
No... I love you!

874
01:09:50,140 --> 01:09:54,310
I will always love only you!

875
01:10:01,140 --> 01:10:02,360
Yuriko...

876
01:10:33,250 --> 01:10:37,910
The knife is the same one she used.

877
01:10:39,370 --> 01:10:41,980
I'm going to kick you out of this shop.

878
01:10:43,000 --> 01:10:44,710
That's what I've decided.

879
01:10:46,800 --> 01:10:49,680
Once that woman was accused of murder,

880
01:10:51,310 --> 01:10:54,600
I thought everything was going
according to plan.

881
01:10:56,220 --> 01:10:57,740
How did this happen?

882
01:11:00,740 --> 01:11:03,540
But the real murderer was not Hideyuki.

883
01:11:04,200 --> 01:11:06,080
Then who?

884
01:11:07,220 --> 01:11:12,540
15 years have passed since the incident
and I still don't know...

885
01:11:12,740 --> 01:11:14,140
It's been a while.

886
01:11:16,310 --> 01:11:17,080
Kyoko-san.

887
01:11:17,480 --> 01:11:19,310
Kyoko-san

888
01:11:19,310 --> 01:11:21,310
You should come light an incense for my father.

889
01:11:24,400 --> 01:11:26,770
That's when I realized it was you.

890
01:11:29,820 --> 01:11:31,020
How ironic.

891
01:11:32,770 --> 01:11:34,440
As a result, I am...

892
01:11:36,000 --> 01:11:39,740
I made your wish come true,
even though I despise you.

893
01:11:40,400 --> 01:11:44,200
But... My mom was falsely accused of a crime!

894
01:11:44,510 --> 01:11:46,620
Why didn't you tell me?

895
01:11:48,600 --> 01:11:50,310
After a suicide attempt,

896
01:11:51,880 --> 01:11:54,160
my mom was getting crazier and crazier.

897
01:11:55,680 --> 01:12:00,310
What would happen if she found out that
her son was a murderer?

898
01:12:00,310 --> 01:12:04,680
It's selfish! My mom lost her loves
and her dreams.

899
01:12:05,340 --> 01:12:08,600
She died alone, in despair!

900
01:12:10,400 --> 01:12:14,850
Why did you appear before Nao-san 15 years
after the murder?

901
01:12:16,620 --> 01:12:21,020
My father suspected that it was the landlady.

902
01:12:21,280 --> 01:12:23,020
He started distancing himself.

903
01:12:24,220 --> 01:12:28,700
And he cares about Yuriko-san...

904
01:12:30,700 --> 01:12:32,700
(To Nao)

905
01:12:32,800 --> 01:12:33,820
From Yuriko-san?

906
01:12:34,600 --> 01:12:36,560
She asked me to do it before she died.

907
01:12:38,200 --> 01:12:42,420
She wants to give it to her daughter
when she turns 20.

908
01:12:43,880 --> 01:12:48,200
She's a descendant of the previous generation.

909
01:12:49,250 --> 01:12:52,220
She's the real successor to Kougetsuan.

910
01:12:53,220 --> 01:12:54,020
Eh?

911
01:12:55,480 --> 01:13:00,000
I made up my mind to turn myself in.

912
01:13:01,140 --> 01:13:03,850
Finally, I decided to look for Nao-chan.

913
01:13:04,900 --> 01:13:06,420
And then I found out

914
01:13:11,770 --> 01:13:16,770
She was making the same warm sweets as Yuriko-san.

915
